      "writtenOn": "2026-02-17T07:22:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s a blocking workaround for Firefox browser behavior\nWhen the user refreshes/closes the page, it triggers a logout action (store.dispatch(\u0027authentication/logout\u0027))\nIn Firefox, the beforeunload event can allow the page to navigate away before async operations complete\nThe 1000-iteration loop with empty console.log() calls creates a synchronous delay to keep the browser \"busy\" long enough for the logout to finish",
      "parentUuid": "02587e60_6b3d64fe",
      "revId": "2a234d63a3cfc1fe73b958248f42b92f33633e0f",
